"_blank\">electromagnetic</a> waves so that a hard wire is not necessary. What does wireless refer to? How is the technology used?<br />\n\tThis week's topic: They changed the wireless setting... (90-110 words)</p>\n<p>\n\tSuggestions:<br />\n\t1) securing a wireless network<br />\n\t2) purchasing a wireless device<br />\n\t3) integrating a wireless device into a network<br />\n\t4) expanding the wireless network<br />\n\t5) Instead of writing a scenario, feel free to comment on the story below.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>范例1：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tOther than audio bugs, he was not sure if there were video surveillance as well. Audio bugs could be planted in more subtle locations, like on the underside of the edge of a surface, as long as they were close to the possible source of the sound, they should work fine. It used to be common practice to put audio bugs inside telephone receivers. Nowadays, however, landlines were not as common since mobile technology was becoming more advanced. Well, bugs on wireless devices, that would be a whole different playing field.</p>\n<p>\n\t想要得到专业主持人的点评和意见吗？<a href=\"http://st.hujiang.com/topic/166912601242/\" target=\"_blank\">快来节目现场一试身手吧&gt;&gt;</a></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p768160/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p768160\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p768128/\">2016两会译员姚梦瑶：颜值又刷新高！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p767113/\">BBC模仿秀: 英国是否脱离欧盟</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p740333/\">囧研究：结婚越晚离婚越快？！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p763072/\">一